        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "## Result\n\nThe NIST SRD-46 database contains **297 ligands** classified under the **\"Amino Acids\"** class.\n\nThis is a large and diverse group, reflecting the wide variety of natural amino acids, their derivatives (e.g., N-methyl, N-acetyl, hydroxyl variants), peptides, and related compounds that have been studied for their metal-binding equilibria. Amino acids are among the most extensively characterized ligand families in coordination chemistry due to their biological importance and their ability to chelate metal ions through amino (–NH₂) and carboxylate (–COO⁻) groups.\n\n*Source: NIST Standard Reference Database 46 (SRD-46)*",
